	r: "acc"
}


NOTE: Account updates are not available to all API developers. For more info please see "Write Access".

Additional Request Data (POST)

The user's API key must be present for all calls to this API.

Using the account API, you can update a user's username, password, or email address. Only one item can be updated per request.

To update the username
&username=[NEW_USERNAME]

JSON
{
	username: [NEW_USERNAME]
}


To update the password
&password=[NEW_PASSWORD]

JSON
{
	password: [NEW_PASSWORD]
}

This should be the raw password, un-hashed.

NOTE: The user's API key is based on the user's password, so if you change the password, you must use the new API key for any future API calls.

To update the email address
&email=[NEW_EMAIL_ADDRESS]

JSON
{
	email: [NEW_EMAIL_ADDRESS]
}


You can also suspend and unsuspend a user, as long as the user has not already been suspended for another reason. This allows the user to close their own account if they wish to.

To suspend a user
&suspend=1

{
	suspend: 1
}

This will suspend the user account for 2 weeks. After 2 weeks the account will be locked and reset, and will be unrecoverable.

To lock a user (WHEN TESTING ONLY, BE VERY CAREFUL)
&suspend=1&asap=1

JSON
{
	suspend: 1,
	asap: 1
}

This will suspend and lock the account immediately and is unrecoverable. Note, this can only be done to accounts which were registered less than an hour ago.

To unsuspend a user
&unsuspend=1

JSON
{
	unsuspend: 1
}
