Transfer Market
Request
To tell the API that this is a request for transfer market information:
&r=tm


By default, all auctions are returned, sorted by nearest deadline first.

Additional Request Data
All of the following requests are optional.

To request a specific sort type:
&sortby=[SORT_BY]

[SORT_BY] can be any of: "name", "price", "deadline", "nationality", "age", or "ranking".

To request a specific sort order:
&sortorder=[SORT_ORDER]

[SORT_ORDER] can be either: "asc", or "desc".

To offset your results:
&offset=[OFFSET]

For example, an offset of 0, will start your results at the first auction in the result set. And an offset of 10 will start your results at the 11th auction.

To limit your results:
&limit=[LIMIT]

For example, a limit of 10, will return a maximum of 10 results.

The offset and limit can, and should be used where possible to reduce the amount of auctions returned at once. For example, &offset=0&limit=10 would return the first 10 auctions, and &offset=10&limit=10 would return auctions 11-20.

To get players from a certain team:
&teamid=[TEAMID]

NOTE: You cannot use any search parameters when getting players from a given team.

Searching

Any and all of the following search criteria can be given:

To search by price:
&priceMin=[PRICE_INTEGER]
and/or
&priceMax=[PRICE_INTEGER]


To search by age:
&ageMin=[AGE_INTEGER]
and/or
&ageMax=[AGE_INTEGER]


To search by CSR:
&csrMin=[CSR_INTEGER]
and/or
&csrMax=[CSR_INTEGER]


To search by Nationality:
&nationality=[COUNTRY_ISO]


To search by player attribute:

First, you must specify an attribute:
&skill[X]=[ATTRIBUTE]

[X] Must be an integer. It can be any integer, e.g. &skill1=

[ATTRIBUTE] can be any of the following: "stamina", "handling", "defense", "attack", "technique", "strength", "jumping", "speed", "agility", "kicking", "form", "height", "weight", "salary", "discipline", "aggression", "leadership", or "experience".

As well as the specified attribute, you must specify either a minimum, or a maximum, or both.
&skill[X]min=[MIN_INTEGER]
and/or
&skill[X]max=[MAX_INTEGER]

[X] Must be the same integer as used for setting the attribute. E.g. &skill1=stamina&skill1min=10

For any attribute with a skill level, you should use the integer level, I.E. Non-existant = 1, Despicable = 2, Horrible = 3, etc.

For height, weight, and salary, you should use the applicable integer.

If any there are no auctions, no information will be returned.

